1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,840
-<i>Watch out!</i>
-<i>What?</i>

2
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:34,640
PREVIOUS EPISODE

3
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:39,120
You think you can fool me
like that, Phupha?

4
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,760
Take this!

5
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,640
Sir, thank you so much

6
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:45,880
for helping get us out of the station.

7
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:48,760
If you want to be a singer,

8
00:02:48,840 --> 00:02:51,120
I'll find another way
to help you pursue your dream.

9
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,880
But if in the future

10
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,560
I become a singer

11
00:02:56,640 --> 00:03:00,440
and someone says
I'm the child of Phupha Thararin,

12
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:03,120
the singer who died because of a scandal,

13
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,880
how would you want me to feel?

14
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:07,920
We won't let her take any more risks.

15
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:10,240
From now on, anything risky,

16
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,480
I'll handle it myself.

17
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,880
Be careful on your way back.

18
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,960
Watch out, in case
you run into Chart again.

19
00:03:19,040 --> 00:03:20,160
I'll be careful.

20
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:31,080
DARATHONG MUSIC

21
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:34,320
Oh?

22
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:38,520
Is this my MV outfit?

23
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,520
Yeah, I've already prepared everything.

24
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:43,280
Let me see. This outfit is nice.

25
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,640
What?

26
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,520
Oh my. Puna!

27
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:49,600
Where did you learn to iron?

28
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,200
The fabric isn't smooth at all!

29
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:54,320
It's all bumpy and full of little patches
all over the place.

30
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,680
Have a look.

31
00:03:58,840 --> 00:03:59,840
Iron it again.

32
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,880
It's all wrinkled. Look at this.

33
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,560
-Iron it again.
-Iron it again.

34
00:04:09,640 --> 00:04:11,080
Iron all of these again.

35
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:15,840
I've already ironed all of these clothes.

36
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,680
-They're still not smooth.
-Yeah.

37
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,800
Just think about it.
If the clothes are wrinkled

38
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:23,320
and the artist wears them
for the MV shoot,

39
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:27,200
the viewers will see it and leave comments
criticizing the company.

40
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,160
What do you think will happen?

41
00:04:29,440 --> 00:04:31,200
The company will be ruined.

42
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,960
It will go out of business because of you!

43
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,000
Definitely.

44
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:37,880
Puna.

45
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,240
You're really pitiful.

46
00:04:44,040 --> 00:04:46,720
Look at me, I'm already so far ahead,

47
00:04:47,960 --> 00:04:49,960
but you're still just a clothes ironer.

48
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,200
So lame.

49
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,640
Right?

50
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:07,480
You have everything.

51
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:10,560
But it's never enough for you.

52
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:12,560
That hurts.

53
00:05:13,280 --> 00:05:15,600
You have to step on others

54
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:17,720
just to feel superior.

55
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,200
Be honest, Maria.

56
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:23,320
Are you really happy doing this?

57
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:24,920
Yes!

58
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:28,040
I'm happy

59
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:31,120
every time I see you
in the place you belong.

60
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:33,920
The position of an ironer,

61
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,480
that's where you belong.

62
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:45,160
It might be true for now.

63
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,760
But just wait, Maria.

64
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:49,840
A clothes ironer like me

65
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:52,760
will rise above you someday.

66
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:03,120
-Wow, she dares to say that.
-Exactly.

67
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,400
Puna, what a dreamer!

68
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:07,760
Looking at her face,

69
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:10,080
there's no way she'll ever be a singer.

70
00:06:10,160 --> 00:06:11,600
-Exactly.
-That's so annoying.

71
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:14,120
-She needs a slap.
-Ouch!

72
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,040
Why did you slap me?

73
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,720
Hello?

74
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:27,280
Let me check for you. Hold on.

75
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:29,240
Hello? Yes.

76
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,520
A kitty!

77
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,240
Aw!

78
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:42,000
So cute. Whose cat is this?

79
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:44,520
Are you hungry?

80
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:46,320
Sorry, whose cat is this?

81
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:50,280
I think this is the real you, Maria.

82
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,600
The real me?

83
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:55,560
A woman who is gentle and kind to animals

84
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:58,800
is not a bad person.

85
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:01,320
Are you saying I'm a bad person?

86
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:06,680
Every time you meet Puna,
you're always so harsh on her.

87
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,520
She's my competitor,
so, of course, I'm harsh.

88
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:19,080
Being competitors doesn't mean
you have to be harsh. You can be kind.

89
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,800
If you beat someone who's skilled,

90
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:25,280
it means you've won with your own ability,

91
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,320
not by stepping on them

92
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:29,920
until they can't fight back.

93
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,480
Hey!

94
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,880
-What are you saying?
-Right.

95
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,600
What are you trying to teach her?

96
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,840
Don't listen, Miss Maria.

97
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,840
If you want to be number one,

98
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,400
remember this.

99
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:50,520
You have to fight to control everything.

100
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,200
Leave them no way to win.

101
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,360
If you can't do it by force, use tricks.

102
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,920
If not by charm, then use spells.

103
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:59,160
Go away!

104
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,680
Hey! If you're so free,
why not go set up the lights

105
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,920
or prepare the set
instead of being in here?

106
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:11,040
Don't let the desire to win

107
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:14,240
cloud the good things in you, Miss Maria.

108
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:21,200
I believe the real you
isn't a bad person at all.

109
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:36,039
-Shoo!
-Go away!

110
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,679
-How dare you lecture others?
-Yeah.

111
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,280
Don't listen to him, Miss Maria.

112
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:43,200
-Don't fall for that nonsense from him.
-Right.

113
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:49,160
Is it possible
that you've secretly fallen for him?

114
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,480
Ridiculous!

115
00:08:51,560 --> 00:08:52,560
No way!

116
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:54,560
Don't even think about it.

117
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:57,840
If Mr. Sonrak finds out
you have feelings for another guy,

118
00:08:57,920 --> 00:08:59,880
he'll turn to Puna.

119
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:03,600
Then, she will rise to become the boss.

120
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:05,160
What?

121
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:07,440
If she becomes our boss,

122
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,720
she'll get revenge on us for sure.

123
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:09,640
Oh no.

124
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,600
No!

125
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,240
I won't let Puna

126
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:16,920
get ahead of me!

127
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:19,640
Way to go!

128
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,720
Yes!

129
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,000
Therefore,

130
00:09:24,080 --> 00:09:27,120
you need to make sure
to win over Mr. Sonrak.

131
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:31,840
Don't forget, you're a famous singer now.

132
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:33,560
The man who's right for you

133
00:09:33,640 --> 00:09:35,480
and who should be your partner

134
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:37,400
is the boss's son,

135
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:40,000
not some loser like Manat.

136
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,840
-Exactly.
-Right?

137
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:01,600
Puna.

138
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,800
I've already ironed all these clothes.

139
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,480
They asked me to iron them again.

140
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,520
Who?

141
00:10:08,760 --> 00:10:09,640
Maria.

142
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:12,840
She's messing with you again.
How can you let her do this?

143
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,520
Let's not have a problem with her.

144
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:15,600
Why?

145
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,800
She's an artist.

146
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,040
I'm not.

147
00:10:20,640 --> 00:10:22,080
It's pointless to argue with her.

148
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:24,520
It's so frustrating! Really frustrating!

149
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:27,320
Puna.

150
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:31,080
Where's the old microphone
for the MV shoot?

151
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,600
Mr. Sonrak asked for it.

152
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:34,680
Go ask the person
who's in charge of the props.

153
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:37,400
We only handle the clothes. We don't know.

154
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:40,800
The props team said Puna
is the one who stored it.

155
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,480
Is that true, Puna?

156
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,760
Yes.

157
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,200
I'll go get it.

158
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:49,360
-I'll help with the ironing.
-Okay.

159
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,320
I'll help too,
or we won't make it in time.

160
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,800
That's good. Here you go.

161
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,240
Chaiya.

162
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:03,720
Someone dropped off a camera lens
the other day, but I wasn't here.

163
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:06,080
I checked, and it's already marked
as delivered.

164
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:08,400
Can you go check and see

165
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:10,040
where it was sent to?

166
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,440
Sure, Mr. Sonrak.

167
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:14,320
You might want to check
the props storage area,

168
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,520
in case it was sent there.

169
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:18,040
-Got it.
-Thank you so much.

170
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,600
Director, hello!

171
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:22,800
Hello, Mr. Sonrak.

172
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:26,120
Mr. Sonrak, you don't
have to call me that.

173
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:28,040
Today, you're the director,

174
00:11:28,120 --> 00:11:30,120
I'm just the assistant.

175
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,720
But I don't know what I'm doing at all.

176
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,200
You'll have to teach me.

177
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:36,800
It's okay, Mr. Sonrak.

178
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:39,480
I'll guide you step by step.

179
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:41,880
But if any reporters come in,

180
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,880
you'll have to take the lead.

181
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:45,520
No problem. I'll take care of it.

182
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,640
In that case, let's start right away.

183
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:58,480
So, they've hidden the stuff here.

184
00:13:19,280 --> 00:13:21,280
DARATHONG MUSIC

185
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,560
Hey!

186
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:29,640
What are you doing here?

187
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:32,600
Calm down.

188
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:35,480
Mr. Sonrak sent me to look for something.

189
00:13:35,560 --> 00:13:36,800
What are you looking for?

190
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:38,200
He ordered a new lens.

191
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,040
But

192
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:42,000
we don't know where it's been stored.

193
00:13:42,080 --> 00:13:44,000
So, I'm checking the logbook

194
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,160
to see who signed for it

195
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,080
and where it's been kept.

196
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:49,960
That's not the right book.

197
00:13:50,040 --> 00:13:51,120
Give it here.

198
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,680
Huh?

199
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:55,520
I didn't know. What's this log for?

200
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,600
Mind your own business.

201
00:13:57,680 --> 00:14:00,600
In that case, why don't you
call Mr. Sonrak and check?

202
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,840
Hello, Boss.

203
00:14:12,080 --> 00:14:14,040
Chaiya's in the warehouse,

204
00:14:15,160 --> 00:14:16,960
saying you sent him to get something.

205
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:22,520
Yes.

206
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:24,680
Understood.

207
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,160
The lens isn't here.

208
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,680
Go look somewhere else.

209
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:35,320
Go!

210
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,560
That was close, Chaiya.

211
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:13,520
Aha!

212
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:18,120
I saw you sneaking into the room earlier.

213
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:22,760
I went in to look for something,
not to sneak around.

214
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:26,440
But the way you acted
seemed a little strange.

215
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:30,280
How was it strange? You think I'm strange?

216
00:15:30,360 --> 00:15:33,000
A normal person
wouldn't take out their phone to film

217
00:15:33,080 --> 00:15:36,800
while looking for something,
like they're collecting evidence.

218
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:41,040
I've got the video.

219
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:46,000
Who are you really, Chaiya?

220
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,640
Didn't you hear me?

221
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:55,000
Tell me right now, who are you really?

222
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:01,200
You don't want to tell me? Fine.

223
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:03,080
But if I had to guess,

224
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:06,120
you're definitely not
just an ordinary YouTuber.

225
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,440
Wow!

226
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,040
Hey.

227
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:17,360
You're good at this!

228
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:19,640
You guessed it scene by scene.

229
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:23,040
Are you Sherlock Holmes or something?
Or have you been watching

230
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:25,560
too many detective series?
I think you have, huh?

231
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:26,840
Stop joking.

232
00:16:29,760 --> 00:16:30,840
Alright.

233
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:32,600
The truth is,

234
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:35,640
I'm not an ordinary YouTuber.

235
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:40,480
See? I knew you'd admit it eventually.

236
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,040
If you know,

237
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:45,000
keep it to yourself.

238
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:46,760
Don't tell anyone.

239
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:50,280
Come on, just say it already.
Stop dragging it out.

240
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:52,200
Come closer.

241
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:02,920
The truth is,

242
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:06,880
I'm a struggling YouTuber.

243
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,079
My channel's been going downhill lately.

244
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:12,160
I wanted to ask you

245
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,520
to be my partner for the channel.

246
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:15,640
You know?

247
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:18,720
You'll make good money
and get paid by the end of the month.

248
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:21,520
Easy work, super chill.

249
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,400
What?

250
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:24,760
You pervert!

251
00:17:24,839 --> 00:17:26,359
What do you mean pervert?

252
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,599
I just wanted to invite you

253
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:30,600
to make a video, sing some songs,
and post them on YouTube. That's it.

254
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:32,440
Hey, wait!

255
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:34,280
Don't tell me you're thinking

256
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:35,880
perverted things about me.

257
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,560
You can't, okay?
I'm still single and innocent!

258
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,240
You can't think like that about me.

259
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:41,840
Just because I look like this,

260
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,960
I still value myself, you know?

261
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,880
What are you talking about?

262
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,560
I'm not thinking anything like that!

263
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,560
Just stop talking.

264
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:50,760
Hey, if you're not thinking that,
why are you blushing?

265
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:52,400
Look!

266
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:54,000
Look at your eyes!

267
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:55,800
They're giving it away.

268
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:58,160
Your eyes look…

269
00:17:58,760 --> 00:18:00,160
so pervy!

270
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:04,400
Don't. Please don't!

271
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:05,920
Don't do anything to me.

272
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,080
Please spare me. I'm scared.

273
00:18:09,760 --> 00:18:11,200
You idiot!

274
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:33,920
Puna.

275
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:37,080
Uh…

276
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,160
Teacher, that's…

277
00:18:39,240 --> 00:18:40,960
I saw everything.

278
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:43,280
Well…

279
00:18:43,360 --> 00:18:44,720
You're here.

280
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:47,080
Did you find the microphone?

281
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:50,160
Uh… Yes, I did.

282
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,800
I thought you couldn't find it. I'll help.

283
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:55,080
-Let's go, Teacher.
-Go where?

284
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,600
Let's just go.

285
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,240
I almost got caught.

286
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,200
Here, Ice. Is this the right microphone?

287
00:19:12,640 --> 00:19:15,280
Exactly! Thanks a lot, Puna.

288
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:17,560
I'll take it to Mr. Sonrak now.

289
00:19:17,640 --> 00:19:23,480
SONRAK DARATHONG

290
00:19:23,560 --> 00:19:25,240
I have something to tell you.

291
00:19:25,880 --> 00:19:26,720
What is it?

292
00:19:28,080 --> 00:19:32,000
I saw Chaiya sneaking into the room
behind the warehouse,

293
00:19:32,080 --> 00:19:33,200
acting kind of strange.

294
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:34,920
How?

295
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:37,400
Well…

296
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:39,440
He was acting suspicious,

297
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:41,840
like he was looking for something.

298
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:42,840
Hey.

299
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,520
He just went in to find something.

300
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,960
But I don't think he's an ordinary person.

301
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:48,960
What do you think he is?

302
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:50,800
Maybe

303
00:19:50,880 --> 00:19:54,200
he's an undercover police captain
or something like that.

304
00:19:54,280 --> 00:19:58,240
Read my lips. Pay attention here.

305
00:19:58,320 --> 00:19:59,440
You're talking nonsense.

306
00:19:59,960 --> 00:20:01,480
You've been watching too many movies.

307
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:03,640
Do you think there are still
undercover police captains

308
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:05,920
these days? Are you out of your mind?

309
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:07,400
Teacher!

310
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:11,120
I don't care if you don't believe me,
but just wait.

311
00:20:11,200 --> 00:20:12,560
From now on,

312
00:20:12,640 --> 00:20:15,920
I'll keep an eye on him
and never take my eyes off him.

313
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:19,120
Are you keeping an eye on him

314
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:22,960
because he's acting strange,
or do you like him?

315
00:20:25,200 --> 00:20:26,360
I don't like him!

316
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,600
It's okay if you like him.

317
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:34,360
Chaiya's actually good-looking.

318
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:36,440
Should I help set you up with him?

319
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:40,640
What are you talking about, Teacher?
I'm not talking to you anymore.

320
00:20:40,720 --> 00:20:43,280
Oh! I've already ironed that one.

321
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:44,840
Huh?

322
00:20:48,600 --> 00:20:49,720
You're blushing.

323
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:52,400
I'll just iron another shirt.

324
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:55,480
I've already ironed that one too.

325
00:20:55,560 --> 00:20:56,880
Come on.

326
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,760
I've ironed them all.
Don't pick up any more.

327
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,760
Teacher!

328
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:11,160
-You're blushing, aren't you?
-Teacher!

329
00:21:16,480 --> 00:21:17,480
Come with me.

330
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:21,800
Superintendent.

331
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:22,720
What is it, Sergeant?

332
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:27,280
Captain Tom is calling in Khod
for questioning.

333
00:21:28,040 --> 00:21:30,240
Did he mention anything about Mr. Singha?

334
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:32,600
Sit down.

335
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:35,040
INVESTIGATING OFFICER

336
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:38,400
What's your name?

337
00:21:39,040 --> 00:21:39,880
Khod.

338
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:42,000
What happened at the market today?

339
00:21:43,160 --> 00:21:44,680
Singha tricked my boss.

340
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:47,880
My boss paid the deposit,
but he wouldn't release the goods.

341
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:50,000
Release the goods? What goods?

342
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:53,920
Oh my, what goods? It's the stuff that he…

343
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,320
Stop right there.

344
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:01,280
What's going on, sir?

345
00:22:01,360 --> 00:22:02,840
You can leave now.

346
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:05,280
I'll question the suspect myself.

347
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,320
But…

348
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,800
Leave. That's an order.

349
00:22:16,720 --> 00:22:18,120
You stay here.

350
00:22:18,920 --> 00:22:20,440
But you need to erase the old records,

351
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:22,200
then we'll start fresh.

352
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:23,240
Yes.

353
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:30,440
Why does he have to interfere with this?

354
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:33,440
I don't get it either.

355
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:40,640
Last question.

356
00:22:42,360 --> 00:22:44,480
Do you have a wife and kids?

357
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:46,720
Yes, I do.

358
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,560
Do you care about them?

359
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,120
Why are you asking, sir?

360
00:22:56,280 --> 00:22:58,320
Just curious, that's all.

361
00:23:07,360 --> 00:23:08,320
Yes.

362
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,080
Please come in.

363
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:12,160
Superintendent.

364
00:23:12,240 --> 00:23:13,560
Mr. Kitti is here.

365
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:14,720
Go open the door for him.

366
00:23:15,360 --> 00:23:16,280
Yes.

367
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,520
So, you are one

368
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,600
of Boss Noo's guys?

369
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:46,040
Please say hello to Mr. Singha for me.

370
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:48,800
I haven't been able to visit him lately.

371
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:50,000
I'll tell him.

372
00:23:50,080 --> 00:23:52,520
He understands you're busy.

373
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,440
Alright, let me walk you out.

374
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:55,520
Sure.

375
00:24:09,560 --> 00:24:11,280
Hey!

376
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:59,240
What happened, Chaiya?

377
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:01,160
Probably Boss Noo's men, sir.

378
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:02,800
They must be here to harm Mr. Sonrak.

379
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:09,040
You're really good at this, Chaiya.

380
00:25:11,040 --> 00:25:11,880
Thank you.

381
00:25:19,080 --> 00:25:20,720
Wow!

382
00:25:20,800 --> 00:25:22,320
Miss Maria.

383
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,840
Your dream has come true.

384
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:25,480
It's so beautiful!

385
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:27,680
Yes! Can I sit here?

386
00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:28,560
Alright, everyone.

387
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:30,160
Gather around.

388
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,440
We're about to start filming for real.

389
00:25:32,480 --> 00:25:33,480
Let's sync up.

390
00:25:33,560 --> 00:25:36,000
I'll start counting down,
then we'll play the music.

391
00:25:36,080 --> 00:25:37,960
Maria, move your mouth
along with the song.

392
00:25:38,040 --> 00:25:40,640
Got it! I'm 100% ready.

393
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,520
It doesn't look like it.

394
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:44,360
You're sweating, Miss Maria.

395
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:45,760
Mr. Sonrak.

396
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:47,200
Could you help wipe her face?

397
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:48,240
Oh…

398
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:49,720
I'm practicing the dance moves.

399
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:51,080
Woo!

400
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:52,040
Okay, sure.

401
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:53,280
Thank you.

402
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:50,400
A CHARMING COUNTRY SINGER

403
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:54,200
SONRAK DARATHONG

404
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:27,080
Wow, so sweet!

405
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:28,400
It's so romantic!

406
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:30,120
That's so sweet.

407
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,680
Everyone, let's go.
We're starting to film now. Come on.

408
00:27:37,120 --> 00:27:38,400
How's it going, Chaiya?

409
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:39,600
DARATHONG MUSIC

410
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:40,600
Yeah, it's fine.

411
00:27:40,680 --> 00:27:43,000
I don't think anyone
will infiltrate today.

412
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:58,000
You look stressed. What's going on?

413
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,560
Nothing. I'm fine.

414
00:28:03,640 --> 00:28:04,720
You're jealous, huh?

415
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:07,080
I'm not jealous.

416
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:08,520
Gotcha!

417
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:12,000
So, you are…

418
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,960
Hey.

419
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:15,720
You smell like a neglected dog!

420
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:19,480
Chaiya.

421
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:22,640
-Follow me.
-Should I go with you?

422
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:23,680
No need.

423
00:28:24,200 --> 00:28:26,600
Stay here and look after Sonrak's safety.

424
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:28,560
Yes, sir.

425
00:28:42,440 --> 00:28:44,880
Five, four, three, two.

426
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:09,680
<i>Who owns this famous music label?</i>
<i>They say the boss</i>

427
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:12,120
<i>Is good-looking</i>

428
00:29:12,200 --> 00:29:18,360
<i>The singers of this label are all handsome</i>
<i>And famous, at the top level</i>

429
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:24,280
<i>I want to be famous, I want to try</i>
<i>I want to be one of the artists</i>

430
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:28,600
<i>I want to be famous</i>
<i>Can't stand it anymore</i>

431
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:31,360
<i>I want people to scream for me</i>
<i>At the stage</i>

432
00:29:31,440 --> 00:29:38,440
<i>Please accept me as an artist</i>
<i>I promise I'll do well</i>

433
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:44,440
<i>No cheating, no running away</i>
<i>I'll sign the contract right away</i>

434
00:29:44,520 --> 00:29:51,440
<i>I want to be famous, like a star</i>
<i>I want everyone to cheer together</i>

435
00:29:51,520 --> 00:29:58,000
<i>I'm serious about being famous</i>
<i>Let the music label fulfill my dream</i>

436
00:29:58,080 --> 00:30:04,760
<i>I want to be famous worldwide</i>
<i>Hoping luck will come, standing by</i>

437
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:11,520
<i>Maybe if I get famous, I'll get lucky</i>
<i>And a police officer will fall for me</i>

438
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:16,520
Sit down.

439
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:25,200
Kitti praised you, saying you're skilled.

440
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:27,840
Before working here, where did you work?

441
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:31,920
I've been a YouTuber since my school days.
This is my first job.

442
00:30:32,560 --> 00:30:35,400
Then where did you train
with guns and combat?

443
00:30:36,800 --> 00:30:41,520
I was an athlete and studied martial arts
since high school.

444
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:42,840
When I got to university,

445
00:30:43,440 --> 00:30:46,440
I joined a shooting club
and learned how to shoot.

446
00:30:47,040 --> 00:30:48,200
I see.

447
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:54,080
Are you brave enough?

448
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:05,080
What would you like me to do, Mr. Singha?

449
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:08,560
I need you to help me with security.

450
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:10,840
Normally, you take care of Mr. Sonrak.

451
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:15,960
But on days when Mr. Singha
goes out of town, he'd like you to help.

452
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:21,320
The people who attacked
Mr. Singha and Mr. Sonrak,

453
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:22,600
who are they?

454
00:31:22,680 --> 00:31:23,560
Well…

455
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:26,120
They're competitors in business.

456
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:27,760
What are their names?

457
00:31:28,920 --> 00:31:30,360
Don't ask too many questions.

458
00:31:32,120 --> 00:31:33,400
You'll find out on your own.

459
00:31:35,920 --> 00:31:38,240
When should I start?

460
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:39,360
Tomorrow.

461
00:31:41,040 --> 00:31:41,920
Alright.

462
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:43,560
Good.

463
00:31:44,080 --> 00:31:45,560
See you tomorrow.

464
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:48,440
Yes, sir.

465
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:50,320
I'll take my leave now.

466
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:04,120
How's the situation with Khod?

467
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:07,120
Give him some time.

468
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:09,640
Let his family visit him.

469
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:12,320
I'm sure he'll make a decision.

470
00:32:27,320 --> 00:32:28,920
Cut!

471
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:32,000
How was it? Is it okay?

472
00:32:32,080 --> 00:32:33,760
Can I see the monitor, please?

473
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:35,640
Sure! Come here.

474
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,160
Come. I'll show you.

475
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,160
Mr. Sonrak.

476
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:41,080
There's a last-minute TV appearance
tomorrow.

477
00:32:42,520 --> 00:32:44,760
Oh, is there any more detail?

478
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:46,200
They'll send the details soon.

479
00:33:05,280 --> 00:33:06,120
Hey!

480
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:09,920
How did you get in here?
This is the men's restroom.

481
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:12,120
Why didn't you tell me

482
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:15,160
that Mr. Sonrak has an interview
for a TV show in Bangkok?

483
00:33:15,840 --> 00:33:17,560
Whoa, I thought it was something else.

484
00:33:20,360 --> 00:33:23,920
What show? Where's the interview?
What time? How long? Tell me everything.

485
00:33:25,600 --> 00:33:28,280
Hey! Are you hard of hearing?

486
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:32,320
I'm not hard of hearing.

487
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,640
I don't know
which question to answer first.

488
00:33:35,240 --> 00:33:37,040
Just answer all my questions!

489
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:42,000
I only know they contacted Mr. Sonrak
to record the show <i>Top Country Hits</i>.

490
00:33:42,920 --> 00:33:43,960
That's all you know?

491
00:33:44,040 --> 00:33:45,800
What kind of bodyguard are you?

492
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:47,720
How do you not know basic info like this?

493
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:50,360
Give me your phone.

494
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:52,400
What for?

495
00:33:52,480 --> 00:33:53,600
Just give it to me.

496
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:04,400
This is the number for Ms. Jang,

497
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:05,840
the show's coordinator.

498
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:08,760
If you want to know anything,
you can call her.

499
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:10,679
-Hey!
-Stop it.

500
00:34:10,760 --> 00:34:12,280
Don't keep asking me.

501
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:14,480
This is all I know. Do you want it or not?

502
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:20,280
Don't forget,

503
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,920
you owe me a meal.

504
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:26,320
Geez!

505
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:36,360
Hello!

506
00:34:36,440 --> 00:34:38,199
Is this Ms. Jang, the coordinator

507
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:40,000
for the <i>Top Country Hits</i> show?

508
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:43,960
Is this really your number?

509
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:46,360
Oh my goodness!

510
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:49,800
Hello, I'm so excited. I happened to get
this number from someone.

511
00:34:49,880 --> 00:34:51,239
Let me introduce myself first.

512
00:34:51,320 --> 00:34:53,360
My name is Sophie.

513
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:55,639
I'm Miss Maria's personal manager.

514
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:57,440
Do you remember her?

515
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:00,360
Yes, she's the one

516
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:02,440
who did the live stream with Mr. Sonrak.

517
00:35:02,520 --> 00:35:06,080
It went viral and trended on Twitter.
Do you remember?

518
00:35:07,680 --> 00:35:08,960
You remember?

519
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:11,320
Oh, thank you so much!

520
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:12,640
Well…

521
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:15,040
I'd like to suggest that we do

522
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:17,560
an interview segment with this couple.
What do you think?

523
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:21,800
Really? You were thinking the same thing?

524
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:23,520
When would be good for you?

525
00:35:24,280 --> 00:35:26,800
Oh, she's free!

526
00:35:26,880 --> 00:35:28,120
Sorry, let me

527
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:30,440
lock in the schedule now.

528
00:35:30,520 --> 00:35:32,120
See you soon.

529
00:35:32,200 --> 00:35:33,480
Goodbye.

530
00:35:33,560 --> 00:35:35,040
Goodbye!

531
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:38,360
-Yay!
-So happy!

532
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:43,160
The shoot's over for today.

533
00:35:43,240 --> 00:35:44,840
Everyone's gone home, right?

534
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:46,160
Yes, they're gone.

535
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:48,200
But you and the teacher

536
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:50,400
have an additional shoot tomorrow as well.

537
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:52,640
What's the shoot for?

538
00:35:53,600 --> 00:35:57,200
Mr. Sonrak and Maria
are recording a show in Bangkok.

539
00:35:57,280 --> 00:35:58,600
Oh no.

540
00:35:58,680 --> 00:36:01,160
You're telling me now,
how can I get the outfits ready?

541
00:36:02,160 --> 00:36:03,440
It's too late!

542
00:36:03,520 --> 00:36:05,040
The stores are all closed.

543
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:06,360
No need to prepare it.

544
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:08,440
I'll have Maria wear the concept outfit.

545
00:36:08,960 --> 00:36:13,000
The outfit was used for the MV shoot today
and hasn't been washed or ironed.

546
00:36:13,080 --> 00:36:16,120
I've already sent it to the dry cleaners,
so you don't have to worry.

547
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:18,520
What about your outfit, Mr. Sonrak?

548
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:21,360
Good point. What should I wear?
Can you pick one for me?

549
00:36:22,240 --> 00:36:23,440
Well…

550
00:36:23,520 --> 00:36:24,480
Let's see.

551
00:36:25,040 --> 00:36:28,160
Which one's good?
Puna, can you help me choose?

552
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:32,320
Go out. Leave.

553
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,560
Oh.

554
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:37,080
I need to talk to you, Teacher.

555
00:36:37,160 --> 00:36:38,920
Let's go and discuss it. Come on.

556
00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:40,640
Let's go.

557
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:43,240
Is this okay? How about this one?

558
00:36:43,320 --> 00:36:44,560
-Let's try it.
-Try it?

559
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:48,920
Puna, please help me with this.

560
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:03,560
How is it?

561
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:06,080
Does it feel tight?

562
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:08,040
It's okay.

563
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:10,240
How about we try buttoning it up?

564
00:37:13,360 --> 00:37:14,680
Let me help you.

565
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:19,480
It's a bit tight.

566
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:22,560
A bit hard to put on.

567
00:37:22,640 --> 00:37:25,240
Okay, it's done. Let's see.

568
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,000
Can you check for me?

569
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:32,280
It's good.

570
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:39,080
Mr. Sonrak.

571
00:37:41,280 --> 00:37:43,320
Mr. Singha is rushing us to go home.

572
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:47,360
Okay, I'll hurry.

573
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:52,240
Bring a lot of outfits tomorrow
so we can try them at the set.

574
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:54,240
Okay.

575
00:37:54,760 --> 00:37:56,280
-Sure.
-Can you help me take it off?

576
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:11,400
I know you're tired, Puna.

577
00:38:13,080 --> 00:38:14,480
I'm here to support you.

578
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:17,440
Thank you.

579
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:07,480
Hey!

580
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:08,520
Who are you?

581
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:41,600
It must be one of Boss Noo's men.

582
00:39:53,120 --> 00:39:54,400
Hey, Yak.

583
00:39:54,960 --> 00:39:56,080
You're not going home yet?

584
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:57,000
Not yet.

585
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:58,240
I'm cleaning the truck

586
00:39:58,320 --> 00:39:59,520
-after driving through mud.
-Oh.

587
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:01,360
Where are you going tomorrow?

588
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:03,320
Taking Mr. Singha on errands
in the morning.

589
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:04,600
Well, okay.

590
00:40:07,240 --> 00:40:08,320
DARATHONG MUSIC

591
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:10,360
You're going to Bangkok
tomorrow morning, right?

592
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:13,320
Yes, you and Manat will go with me.

593
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:15,240
Chaiya will go with my father.

594
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:17,080
My father called and said
he wanted to take you along.

595
00:40:17,600 --> 00:40:18,440
Yes.

596
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:20,360
Where are you taking the boss tomorrow?

597
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:23,240
I don't know.
Mr. Singha hasn't told me yet.

598
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:26,120
Go home already. You guys keep talking.

599
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:28,400
-I'll drive.
-Let's go.

600
00:40:44,120 --> 00:40:46,720
Shoot, I forgot the sponge.

601
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:48,320
Ugh.

602
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:57,440
-Here, take it.
-Thank you, Pleaw.

603
00:40:57,520 --> 00:41:00,000
You're the driver
for Darathong Music, right?

604
00:41:00,600 --> 00:41:02,320
Yes, but I'm not a full-time employee.

605
00:41:02,400 --> 00:41:03,560
I only come when I'm called.

606
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:05,240
What do you want me to do?

607
00:41:05,320 --> 00:41:06,200
Tomorrow,

608
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:09,600
Yak, Singha's regular driver,
is taking sick leave.

609
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:10,640
Really?

610
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:11,880
You need to fill in for him.

611
00:41:12,760 --> 00:41:13,920
-But…
-No buts.

612
00:41:14,520 --> 00:41:16,280
If I say go, you go.

613
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:17,840
Okay.

614
00:41:18,400 --> 00:41:21,440
Whenever you leave Khok Ta Yu tomorrow,

615
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:23,040
turn into Nern Maprao immediately.

616
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:24,520
What are you going to do?

617
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:26,000
You don't need to know.

618
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:28,760
Just take him to Nern Maprao.

619
00:41:29,480 --> 00:41:30,800
Otherwise,

620
00:41:32,120 --> 00:41:34,000
I'll visit your family.

621
00:41:34,520 --> 00:41:35,560
Alright, okay.

622
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:37,880
I'll do it.

623
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:46,760
-Go!
-Yes.

624
00:42:19,520 --> 00:42:20,480
Who sent the message?

625
00:42:20,560 --> 00:42:22,080
Uncle Sergeant's informant.

626
00:42:22,160 --> 00:42:24,520
He texted saying an unexpected event

627
00:42:24,600 --> 00:42:26,400
will take place tomorrow near Dong Maprao.

628
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:28,360
Unexpected event?

629
00:42:31,600 --> 00:42:32,800
Where is Singha going tomorrow?

630
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:35,560
He still won't tell me the route.

631
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:40,080
I'm going to the city, taking Sonrak
and Maria to record a show.

632
00:42:42,160 --> 00:42:43,960
If he doesn't attack Sonrak,

633
00:42:44,840 --> 00:42:46,200
he'll attack Singha.

634
00:42:47,280 --> 00:42:49,200
If not you, then it'll be me.

635
00:42:54,600 --> 00:42:55,760
Sathu.

636
00:42:57,120 --> 00:43:01,360
Please help me, Uncle Sergeant.
Whoever it is, just not me.

637
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:05,040
Hey, Manat!

638
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:06,640
-What?
-You jerk!

639
00:43:06,720 --> 00:43:08,880
If it's not you, then it's me!

640
00:43:08,960 --> 00:43:11,040
Oh, I hope you come back safe too.

641
00:43:11,120 --> 00:43:12,360
Ah.

642
00:43:13,880 --> 00:43:15,080
Wait, what are you doing?

643
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:18,560
Uncle Sergeant.

644
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:21,200
If you're annoyed with anyone,

645
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:23,640
give them a hard time.

646
00:43:23,720 --> 00:43:26,200
Give me an easy job, Uncle.

647
00:43:29,120 --> 00:43:30,160
Hey!

648
00:43:30,240 --> 00:43:31,520
My dear friend Chaiya.

649
00:43:31,600 --> 00:43:33,480
Why don't you sacrifice for your friend?

650
00:43:33,560 --> 00:43:35,560
This is me sacrificing!

651
00:43:35,640 --> 00:43:36,880
-Really?
-Yeah!

652
00:43:36,960 --> 00:43:38,000
Why does it have to be me?

653
00:43:38,680 --> 00:43:39,880
You need to suffer a bit too!

654
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:51,280
DARATHONG MUSIC

655
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:54,440
Where's Yak?

656
00:43:54,520 --> 00:43:56,800
Well, Yak's not feeling well, sir.

657
00:43:56,880 --> 00:43:58,720
The company sent me to drive instead.

658
00:43:58,800 --> 00:44:00,240
Do you know the way?

659
00:44:00,320 --> 00:44:01,280
Yes, I do.

660
00:44:04,040 --> 00:44:06,040
Where are we going today, sir?

661
00:44:06,120 --> 00:44:07,240
We're going for a meeting.

662
00:44:08,280 --> 00:44:10,000
But the route is a bit isolated,

663
00:44:10,080 --> 00:44:11,400
so I asked you to come along.

664
00:44:56,960 --> 00:44:57,960
Hey!

665
00:44:58,520 --> 00:44:59,680
Why did you bring us this way?

666
00:45:04,680 --> 00:45:05,840
Chaiya!

667
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:07,960
Stop!

668
00:45:08,040 --> 00:45:08,960
Let go!

669
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:09,960
Stop!

670
00:45:10,040 --> 00:45:10,840
Let go!

671
00:45:10,920 --> 00:45:12,080
Hey!

672
00:45:12,160 --> 00:45:13,120
Stop the car!

673
00:45:13,200 --> 00:45:14,600
No!

674
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:15,960
Hey!

675
00:45:16,720 --> 00:45:17,520
Ugh!

676
00:45:17,600 --> 00:45:18,840
-Let go!
-Hey!

677
00:45:18,920 --> 00:45:19,840
Ugh!

678
00:45:32,160 --> 00:45:33,120
Get out!

679
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:43,960
Who sent you?

680
00:45:44,040 --> 00:45:45,800
A man named Pleaw.

681
00:45:45,880 --> 00:45:47,440
He hired me to bring you here.

682
00:45:48,920 --> 00:45:50,080
Captain!

683
00:45:58,600 --> 00:45:59,440
Mr. Singha.

684
00:45:59,520 --> 00:46:00,440
It's okay.

685
00:46:01,040 --> 00:46:02,160
I can handle it.

686
00:46:21,920 --> 00:46:23,400
Let's go, Mr. Singha. Go!

687
00:46:37,480 --> 00:46:38,400
Go!

688
00:46:43,200 --> 00:46:45,040
Hello. Is this the police?

689
00:46:45,920 --> 00:46:47,400
Please send officers
to handle the situation.

690
00:46:48,200 --> 00:46:50,560
Captain, there's a clash happening.

691
00:46:50,640 --> 00:46:51,600
We're not sure who's involved.

692
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:53,280
A local resident reported it.

693
00:46:53,360 --> 00:46:54,720
What's the location?

694
00:46:54,800 --> 00:46:56,080
Near the Nern Maprao village.

695
00:46:56,160 --> 00:46:57,600
Assemble a team and take me there.

696
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:58,840
Yes, sir.

697
00:47:03,480 --> 00:47:05,080
-What's up, Sergeant?
-Hey, Chit!

698
00:47:05,160 --> 00:47:08,600
There's a shooting
happening near Nern Maprao.

699
00:47:08,680 --> 00:47:09,960
Is it your guys?

700
00:47:10,040 --> 00:47:11,400
It's not us.

701
00:47:11,480 --> 00:47:13,680
But wait, near Nern Maprao?

702
00:47:18,160 --> 00:47:19,760
So, do you know

703
00:47:19,840 --> 00:47:21,080
<i>who they are?</i>

704
00:47:21,600 --> 00:47:22,840
It might be Mr. Singha,

705
00:47:23,520 --> 00:47:24,680
since he's passing by there today.

706
00:47:24,760 --> 00:47:27,320
Then hurry up and help Mr. Singha

707
00:47:27,400 --> 00:47:29,200
before the police get there.

708
00:47:29,280 --> 00:47:31,400
Thanks, Sergeant. I'll go right now.

709
00:47:32,000 --> 00:47:34,400
Chart, the boss is in trouble.

710
00:47:34,480 --> 00:47:35,800
Near Nern Maprao?

711
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:37,040
-Let's go.
-Let's go!

712
00:47:49,960 --> 00:47:52,080
Mr. Singha, do you have any bullets left?

713
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:53,040
None left.

714
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:03,160
Grenade!

715
00:48:09,240 --> 00:48:12,040
If you win, are you truly happy…

716
00:48:12,120 --> 00:48:13,120
NEXT EPISODE

717
00:48:13,200 --> 00:48:15,120
…with a victory that comes
from hurting others?

718
00:48:16,320 --> 00:48:18,200
But I'm an artist.

719
00:48:18,920 --> 00:48:19,960
And you,

720
00:48:20,040 --> 00:48:21,640
you're just a clothes ironer.

721
00:48:21,720 --> 00:48:23,200
Ugh!

722
00:48:23,280 --> 00:48:24,160
I can't take it anymore!

723
00:48:25,080 --> 00:48:26,200
Are you scared?

724
00:48:27,320 --> 00:48:29,800
Step back. Hey, don't come any closer!

725
00:48:29,880 --> 00:48:30,840
Come here!

726
00:48:31,560 --> 00:48:35,600
<i>Who owns this famous music label?</i>
<i>They say the boss</i>

727
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:38,200
<i>Is good-looking</i>

728
00:48:41,160 --> 00:48:42,400
Puna.

729
00:48:42,480 --> 00:48:44,120
Who are you guys really?

730
00:51:45,400 --> 00:51:47,680
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
